<section class="block-section do">
  <span class="section-tag">Do</span>
  <h2>Today's work — choose one path</h2>
  <p class="sub">All four paths end the same way: a labeled photo set or photo response that identifies specific weathering processes. The path you pick is about where you do the work.</p>
  <div class="callout sketch-first">
    <div class="callout-title">Sketch first — no words</div>
    <p>Sketch first, no words (5 min, alone): one drawing that shows the DIFFERENCE between weathering and erosion. Compare with a partner (3 min): can they tell which side is which without you explaining? Journal it, dated — today's work sharpens exactly this distinction.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="choice-intro">
    <strong>Learning Intention:</strong> {{ learningIntention | safe }}
  </div>
  <div class="choice-board">
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">A</div>
      <div class="choice-title">8-photo identification (default)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Pair work. Eight unfamiliar field photos. For each, identify the dominant weathering process and the single best piece of visual evidence. Pair discussion encouraged; submit one annotated set per pair.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Pairs · Default</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">B</div>
      <div class="choice-title">AISC campus weathering walk</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Walk the AISC campus (or specific zone Mr. Ignash assigns). Photograph 3 weathering processes on the way. Label each with mechanism + evidence. Stretch: identify one example of chemical weathering specifically.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Stretch</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">C</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Tropical-specific deep dive</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Research how laterite forms in tropical climates. Why is laterite so common in South India? Produce a half-page explainer with one diagram. Useful prep for Block 5's tropical-landscapes content.</div>
